# Getting Started

This guide walks you through cloning Configra, building the workspace,
and running the test suite. It is derived from the project
[`README.md`](https://github.com/KooshaPari/Configra) and
[`Cargo.toml`](https://github.com/KooshaPari/Configra/blob/main/Cargo.toml).

## Prerequisites

- **Rust** `>= 1.75` (workspace MSRV — see `[workspace.package].rust-version`
  in `Cargo.toml`).
- **Cargo** (ships with Rust).
- A C toolchain for the SQLite-backed crates if you enable those features.

## Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/KooshaPari/Configra.git
cd Configra
```

## Workspace layout

Configra is a **Cargo workspace** with four tier-2 sub-crates, each with
its own concern (ADR-022 / ADR-031):

```
Configra/                                  v0.4.0 (workspace)
├── crates/
│   ├── pheno-config/                      typed runtime Config + ConfigBuilder
│   ├── settly/                            settings lifecycle (validation, migration)
│   ├── config-schema/                     JSON schema validation primitives
│   └── phenotype-config-loader/           generic JSON/TOML file loaders
├── docs/                                  this VitePress site
├── typescript/packages/conft/             TS edge layer
└── Cargo.toml                             workspace manifest
```

Workspace dependencies (pinned in `Cargo.toml`):

```toml
[workspace.dependencies]
tokio = { version = "1", features = ["full"] }
async-trait = "0.1"
serde = { version = "1", features = ["derive"] }
serde_json = "1"
toml = "0.8"
thiserror = "2"
anyhow = "1"
uuid = { version = "1", features = ["v4", "serde"] }
chrono = "0.4"
tempfile = "3"
criterion = "0.5"
tracing = "0.1"
```

## Build the workspace

```bash
cargo build --workspace
```

For an optimized build:

```bash
cargo build --workspace --release
```

## Run the tests

```bash
cargo test --workspace
```

## Lint and format

The CI pipeline enforces `cargo fmt --check` and
`cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`. Run them
locally before pushing:

```bash
cargo fmt --all
cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings
```

## Tier-2 quality bar

Every sub-crate must ship:

- `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `AGENTS.md`
- `cargo clippy -- -D warnings`
- ≥ 80 % line coverage (ADR-040)

## A minimal end-to-end snippet

The following is illustrative pseudocode for loading a typed config —
the real API lives in each crate's `lib.rs`. Tokens below are
**placeholders**, not real credentials:

```rust
// pseudo-code — exact API lives in crates/pheno-config
use pheno_config::{Config, ConfigBuilder};

let cfg = ConfigBuilder::new()
    .load_toml("Config.toml")?              // see phenotype-config-loader
    .overlay_env("MYAPP_")?                 // MYAPP_FOO=bar -> foo = "bar"
    .validate_with(config_schema::schema()) // see config-schema
    .build()?;

assert_eq!(cfg.get("api_token"), "YOUR_API_TOKEN");
```

For deeper guides, see the source-repo migration notes in
[`docs/migrations/`](https://github.com/KooshaPari/Configra/tree/main/docs/migrations).

